  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Grandmothers and teachers together for education</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As a result of COVID-19, children will have lost  eight months of school. In response to this tragic situation, grandmothers and teachers will join hands in a summer learning program to support children in rural southern Senegal. GMP aims to expand its innovative Summer Learning Program to fill the gap caused by COVID-19. 32 teachers and grandmothers will organize a fun program of traditional games and stories combined with a robust review of French and math before school restarts in the fall.</narrative>
  </description>
